subSubSection.paragraph:
Gonopods.
Right gonopod structure as follows: coxa with lateral swelling at midlength absent (
Fig. 23A, C
); acropodite elongated, about four times as long as prefemur; median region expanded, cup-shaped in ventral view, with a concavity and cavity (
Fig. 23D
); distal region of acropodite strongly sinuous, bifurcate, curved ventrally at a 75° angle (
Fig. 23A–D
); VP1 emarginated on posterior region, evident, exceeding the width of ventral region of acropodite, in lateral view (
Fig. 23A, C
); VP2 absent; LP1 long and wide, projected towards the lateral region of gonopod, aculeate margins; LP2, LP3 and DP absent (
Fig. 23A–D
). Opening of solenomere located at distal end of acropodite, at bifurcation. Solenomere tapering, hooked, projected towards the acropodital apical region (
Fig. 23A, B
).
